        "subject": "LU-19553 dkms: inject depends on other dkms packages",
        "message": "LU-19553 dkms: inject depends on other dkms packages\n\nWhen mlnx-ofed-kernel-dkms has been installed but not yet\nbuilt (new kernel has not yet booted) installing\nlustre-client-dkms\nfails to build correctly (due to building against an old set\nof symbols).\n\nThis is theoretically true for several other possible\npackages that lustre could be depending upon.\n\nmlnx-ofed-kernel\nzfs\ncray-kfabric (and its dependencies)\n  [cray-cxi-driver, cray-slingshot-base-link, kdreg2, sl-driver]\n\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-12975\nTest-Parameters: trivial testgroup=full-dkms\nSigned-off-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ib2e4d25ed16932949c5314ae13939b5e1215e8ec\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62161\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Jian Yu <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
